questions__question_text: What is the worst-case time complexity of the QuickSort algorithm?
questions__explanation: In the worst case, QuickSort performs O(n^2) comparisons when the pivot always results in the most unbalanced partitions.

questions__question_text: Evaluate the integral ∫(2x dx) from 0 to 2.
questions__explanation: The integral of 2x is x^2. Evaluating from 0 to 2, we get 2^2 - 0^2 = 4.

questions__question_text: Which of the following are regular languages?
questions__options__A: Set of all palindromes over {a, b}
questions__options__B: Set of all strings of even length over {a, b}
questions__options__C: Set of all binary strings with an equal number of 0s and 1s
questions__options__D: Set of all strings that do not contain the substring 'aa'
questions__explanation: Option B is regular because even-length strings can be represented by a finite state machine. Option D is also regular because it can be recognized by a DFA.

questions__question_text: What is the probability of getting exactly two heads when flipping three fair coins?
questions__explanation: The sample space is {HHH, HHT, HTH, HTT, THH, THT, TTH, TTT}. The favorable cases are {HHT, HTH, THH}, which is 3 out of 8.

questions__question_text: Which of the following are properties of a binary search tree (BST)?
questions__options__A: The left subtree contains only nodes with values less than the parent node.
questions__options__B: The right subtree contains only nodes with values greater than the parent node.
questions__options__C: There are no duplicate values in the BST.
questions__options__D: The height of a balanced BST is always O(n).
questions__explanation: Options A, B, and C are properties of a BST. Option D is incorrect because the height of a balanced BST is O(log n), not O(n).

questions__question_text: A CPU has a 5-stage pipeline. If a program has 100 instructions, how many cycles will it take to complete execution assuming no stalls?
questions__explanation: The first instruction takes 5 cycles to complete, and each subsequent instruction takes 1 cycle. Total cycles = (n + (k-1)) = 100 + 4 = 104.

questions__question_text: Which of the following statements about NP-complete problems are true?
questions__options__A: All NP-complete problems are solvable in polynomial time.
questions__options__B: If one NP-complete problem is solved in polynomial time, all NP-complete problems can be solved in polynomial time.
questions__options__C: NP-complete problems are a subset of NP-hard problems.
questions__options__D: The P vs NP question asks whether every problem in P is also in NP.
questions__explanation: NP-complete problems are the hardest problems in NP, and if one can be solved in polynomial time, then all can be. NP-complete problems are also a subset of NP-hard problems.

questions__question_text: A relation R is reflexive if and only if:
questions__options__A: For every element a in the set, (a, a) '/∈' R.
questions__options__B: For every (a, b) in R, (b, a) '∈' R.
questions__options__C: For every (a, b) and (b, c) in R, (a, c) '∈' R.
questions__options__D: For every element a in the set, there exists b such that (a, b) ∈ R.
questions__explanation: A relation R is reflexive if every element is related to itself, meaning (a, a) ∈ R for all elements a.

questions__question_text: What is the number of edges in a complete graph with 'n' vertices?
questions__explanation: A complete graph with 'n' vertices has edges between every pair of vertices. The number of edges is given by n(n-1)/2.

questions__question_text: Which of the following protocols work at the transport layer of the OSI model?
questions__explanation: TCP and UDP are transport layer protocols, while IP is a network layer protocol and FTP is an application layer protocol.

questions__question_text: The decimal equivalent of the binary number 1011.01 is:
questions__explanation: 1011 in decimal is 11 and .01 in binary represents 0.25, so the total value is 11.25.

questions__question_text: What is the probability of getting at least one head when flipping two fair coins?
questions__explanation: The probability of getting no heads (only tails) is (1/2 * 1/2 = 1/4). Thus, the probability of getting at least one head is 1 - 1/4 = 3/4 = 0.75.

questions__question_text: Which of the following are NP-complete problems?
questions__explanation: The Travelling Salesman Problem, SAT, and Subset Sum Problem are all NP-complete problems, while Dijkstra’s algorithm runs in polynomial time.

questions__question_text: Which of the following are correct regarding AVL trees?
questions__options__A: AVL tree is a self-balancing binary search tree.
questions__options__B: The height difference between left and right subtrees is at most 2.
questions__options__C: AVL trees provide better search performance than unbalanced binary search trees.
questions__options__D: Insertion and deletion in an AVL tree take O(log n) time.
questions__explanation: AVL trees are self-balancing BSTs with a height difference of at most 1 between left and right subtrees. They provide O(log n) search, insertion, and deletion.
